Wrinklies need not apply
12:01AM BST 16 Oct 2006
Comments
In an admirably swift response to the Government's latest anti-discrimination gimmick, the recruitment agency Robert Walters has outlawed from its advertisements any words, such as "energetic" or "experienced", that might imply prejudice against a certain age group. The list, which also includes "hungry" and "gravitas", is imaginative, but not, we feel, exhaustive. "Literate" or "knowledgeable", for example, would surely deter most applicants under 30. Meanwhile, the first of the new generation of recruitment ads, commissioned by the Government itself, has fallen into our hands. "Someone needed to redraft sloppily worded legislation that will subject thousands of employers to needless inconvenience and make the law a laughing stock. If you can read this without moving your lips, you might just be the person we're looking for." Telegraph View
